{
    "level": "A1",
    "intro": "Aby zrobić przeczenie z <strong>to be</strong>, wstaw <strong>not</strong> po <strong>am / is / are</strong>.",
    "rules": [
        {
            "label": "am not",
            "color": "emerald",
            "text": "Z <strong>I</strong> używaj <strong>am not</strong>.",
            "example": "I am not tired."
        },
        {
            "label": "is not / isn't",
            "color": "blue",
            "text": "Z <strong>he / she / it</strong> używaj <strong>is not</strong> albo <strong>isn't</strong>.",
            "example": "She isn't busy."
        },
        {
            "label": "are not / aren't",
            "color": "amber",
            "text": "Z <strong>you / we / they</strong> używaj <strong>are not</strong> albo <strong>aren't</strong>.",
            "example": "They aren't at home."
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "1. Formy przeczące",
    "intro": "Pełna forma przydaje się do mocniejszego akcentu, skrócona jest częsta w codziennej mowie.",
    "items": [
        {
            "label": "I",
            "title": "am not",
            "subtitle": "I am not late."
        },
        {
            "label": "He / She / It",
            "title": "is not / isn't",
            "subtitle": "He is not hungry. / He isn't hungry."
        },
        {
            "label": "You / We / They",
            "title": "are not / aren't",
            "subtitle": "We are not ready. / We aren't ready."
        },
        {
            "label": "Pattern",
            "title": "Subject + be + not",
            "subtitle": "She is not here. / They are not students."
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "2. Jak to działa",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "Pełna forma",
            "color": "emerald",
            "description": "Pełnej formy często używamy wtedy, gdy chcemy zabrzmieć wyraźniej albo mocniej podkreślić przeczenie.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "She is not at school.",
                    "ua": "Ona nie jest w szkole."
                },
                {
                    "en": "We are not tired.",
                    "ua": "Nie jesteśmy zmęczeni."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Skrócona forma",
            "color": "blue",
            "description": "W zwykłej rozmowie częściej pojawiają się <strong>isn't</strong> i <strong>aren't</strong>.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "He isn't busy.",
                    "ua": "On nie jest zajęty."
                },
                {
                    "en": "They aren't my friends.",
                    "ua": "Oni nie są moimi przyjaciółmi."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Kontrast z twierdzeniem",
            "color": "amber",
            "description": "Porównuj zdanie twierdzące i przeczące, żeby szybko zobaczyć miejsce <strong>not</strong>.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "She is ready. → She isn't ready.",
                    "ua": "not stoi po is."
                },
                {
                    "en": "They are at home. → They aren't at home.",
                    "ua": "not stoi po are."
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "3. Twierdzenie vs przeczenie",
    "intro": "Forma to be zostaje w zdaniu: dodajemy tylko <strong>not</strong>.",
    "rows": [
        {
            "en": "I am at home.",
            "ua": "I am not at home.",
            "note": "am + not"
        },
        {
            "en": "She is happy.",
            "ua": "She isn't happy.",
            "note": "isn't = is not"
        },
        {
            "en": "They are students.",
            "ua": "They aren't students.",
            "note": "aren't = are not"
        }
    ],
    "warning": "📌 Nie dodawaj <strong>do / does</strong> do przeczeń z <strong>to be</strong>."
}

{
    "title": "4. Typowe błędy",
    "items": [
        {
            "label": "Błąd 1",
            "color": "rose",
            "title": "Stawianie not przed formą to be.",
            "wrong": "❌ She not is tired.",
            "right": "✅ <span class=\"font-mono\">She is not tired.</span>"
        },
        {
            "label": "Błąd 2",
            "color": "amber",
            "title": "Dodawanie do do to be.",
            "wrong": "❌ They don't are ready.",
            "right": "✅ <span class=\"font-mono\">They aren't ready.</span>"
        },
        {
            "label": "Błąd 3",
            "color": "sky",
            "title": "Mieszanie am not z isn't / aren't.",
            "wrong": "❌ I isn't late.",
            "right": "✅ <span class=\"font-mono\">I am not late.</span>"
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "5. Krótkie podsumowanie",
    "items": [
        "Przeczenie z <strong>to be</strong> = <strong>am / is / are + not</strong>.",
        "Z <strong>I</strong> używaj <strong>am not</strong>.",
        "Z <strong>he / she / it</strong> używaj <strong>is not</strong> albo <strong>isn't</strong>.",
        "Z <strong>you / we / they</strong> używaj <strong>are not</strong> albo <strong>aren't</strong>.",
        "W przeczeniach z <strong>to be</strong> nie potrzebujesz <strong>do / does</strong>."
    ]
}

